Make the copy of MYMETA.json into blib/meta/ optional.

App::cpm::Builder::Base::_write_blib_meta unconditionally copies
MYMETA.json and dies if it is missing. Some distributions (notably those
built from a tarball without a MYMETA.json, or non-EU::MM builds) do not
produce one, which aborts the install. Guard the copy on the file's
existence so it is skipped instead of fatal.

Upstream: https://github.com/skaji/cpm  lib/App/cpm/Builder/Base.pm

--- a/lib/App/cpm/Builder/Base.pm
+++ b/lib/App/cpm/Builder/Base.pm
@@ -123,7 +123,7 @@ sub _write_blib_meta ($self, $ctx) {
         close $fh;
     }

-    File::Copy::copy("MYMETA.json", "blib/meta/MYMETA.json") or die $!;
+    File::Copy::copy("MYMETA.json", "blib/meta/MYMETA.json") or die $! if -f "MYMETA.json";
     return 1;
 }

